Create the Map 11


Create the Map





This part of the Dashboard is made up of 5 elements: 2 maps, 1 text boxes, 1 card, and a picture for the legend.

 



Step 9.1 – Create the Large Map visualization

Copy the large map from the Race Tp page.

Paste it on the Dashboard page.

In the field Location, remove City and Replace it with State.

Remove the filed in Legend and leave it blank.

Remove the Tooltip field and leave it blank.




Use the flowing picture to set the size and the coordinates.





Create the following measures:

.Total Shootings SoFar = CALCULATE([.Total Shootings], ALLSELECTED(DimState[State]))

.SoFar % Shootings = [.Total Shootings]/[.Total Shootings SoFar]

 

In the format tab, go to the Data Colors tab and click on the fx button.





Make the following selections:





In the format tab, go to the Bubbles tab and set the size -10.





Change the title size to 12.

Turn off the Border.

 

 


Step 9.2 – Create the Small Map visualization

Just like before, copy the large map and paste it.

Change the title to Hawaii size 8.

In the filters tab, select only Hawaii.

Change the size and the coordinates.






Step 9.3 – Create the Map color legend.

Use the picture attached in the files or create one by taking a screenshot from the one autogenerated in the Data Colors tab.




Insert the picture and modify the size and the coordinates.






Step 9.4 – Map legend text box.

Insert a text box.

Type in or copy and paste the following text:


Low                   (Shootings %)                   High

The size of the bubble represents the number of victims.



Change the size and coordinates.





Turn on the Shadow option.




Step 9.5 –Create the Timeline card.

Insert a card.

Create the following measure:   .Timeline = "Timeline"

Add the measure to the card.

Change the size and the coordinates.





Change the color of the data label to the blue that has been used all along (#12239e).

Change the font size to 10.

Turn of the Category.

Turn on the border option and change the color to blue.

 



Step 9.6 – Map Tooltips

Create a duplicate of the page Weapon Type and rename it Map TP.

The 1st card with the weapon column needs to be replace with the column State.

Delete the card Victims Per Shooting.

Delete the small map.

Change the Legend of the map from Weapon to ShootingID.

Remove Total Victims from the Size field.

Remove Hawaii from the State filter.

Apply the following size and coordinates to the State card.





Change the data label font size to 20.

Change the Page size from 350 to 385.

Apply the following size and coordinates to the Shootings and Victims Per Shooting cards.





Change the title font size to 13 for both cards.

Apply the following size and coordinates to the Map visualization.





Turn off the Map title.

Turn on the Category labels

Change the font size to 8.

Change the background color to blue with 50% transparency.





Go back to the Dashboard page and make sure to activate this tooltip on both maps.

On this page, make sure to activate the Shadow option only for the large map.

Also activate the zoom buttons.





At this point the Dashboard should look like this:
